#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.digitize.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.digitize"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:1 of
msgid ""
"Return the indices of the bins to which each value in input tensor "
"belongs."
msgstr "返回输入张量中每个值所属的区间索引。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:3 of
msgid ""
"Each index ``i`` returned is such that ``bins[i-1] <= x < bins[i]`` if "
"`bins` is monotonically increasing, or ``bins[i-1] > x >= bins[i]`` if "
"`bins` is monotonically decreasing. If values in `x` are beyond the "
"bounds of `bins`, 0 or ``len(bins)`` is returned as appropriate. If right"
" is True, then the right bin is closed so that the index ``i`` is such "
"that ``bins[i-1] < x <= bins[i]`` or ``bins[i-1] >= x > bins[i]`` if "
"`bins` is monotonically increasing or decreasing, respectively."
msgstr ""
"返回的每个索引 ``i`` 满足：若 `bins` 单调递增，则 ``bins[i-1] <= x < bins"
"[i]``；若 `bins` 单调递减，则 ``bins[i-1] > x >= bins[i]``。如果 `x` 中的"
"值超出了 `bins` 的范围，则根据情况返回 0 或 ``len(bins)``。如果 right 为 "
"True，则右区间为闭区间，使得索引 ``i`` 满足：若 `bins` 单调递增，则 ``"
"bins[i-1] < x <= bins[i]``；若 `bins` 单调递减，则 ``bins[i-1] >= x > "
"bins[i]``。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:11 of
msgid "Input tensor to be binned."
msgstr "待分箱的输入张量。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:13 of
msgid "Array of bins. It has to be 1-dimensional and monotonic."
msgstr "区间数组。必须是一维且单调的。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:15 of
msgid ""
"Indicating whether the intervals include the right or the left bin edge. "
"Default behavior is (right==False) indicating that the interval does not "
"include the right edge. The left bin end is open in this case, i.e., "
"bins[i-1] <= x < bins[i] is the default behavior for monotonically "
"increasing bins."
msgstr ""
"表示区间是否包含右边界或左边界。默认行为是 (right==False)，表示区间不包含"
"右边界。此时左区间端点是开区间，即对于单调递增的区间，bins[i-1] <= x < "
"bins[i] 是默认行为。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:22 of
msgid "**out** -- Output tensor of indices, of same shape as `x`."
msgstr "**out** -- 索引输出张量，形状与 `x` 相同。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize of
msgid "抛出"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:25 of
msgid "If `bins` is not monotonic."
msgstr "如果 `bins` 不是单调的。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:26 of
msgid "If the type of the input is complex."
msgstr "如果输入的类型是复数。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:28 of
msgid ""
":py:obj:`bincount`, :py:obj:`histogram`, :py:obj:`unique`, "
":py:obj:`searchsorted`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:31 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:32 of
msgid ""
"If values in `x` are such that they fall outside the bin range, "
"attempting to index `bins` with the indices that `digitize` returns will "
"result in an IndexError."
msgstr ""
"如果 `x` 中的值超出了区间范围，使用 `digitize` 返回的索引去访问 `bins` 会"
"导致 IndexError。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.digitize.digitize:36 of
msgid ""
"`mt.digitize` is  implemented in terms of `mt.searchsorted`. This means "
"that a binary search is used to bin the values, which scales much better "
"for larger number of bins than the previous linear search. It also "
"removes the requirement for the input array to be 1-dimensional."
msgstr ""
"`mt.digitize` 是基于 `mt.searchsorted` 实现的。这意味着使用二分查找来对值"
"进行分箱，在区间数量较大时比以前的线性搜索性能更好。它还取消了输入数组"
"必须是一维的要求。"

